    "caption": "Two eyes pointing different directions and a tongue faster than a sneeze.",
    "shortDescription": "Chameleons are famous for changing color, but it's not really about camouflage — they shift colors to show their mood, temperature, and what they think of the chameleon next to them. Each eye swivels around completely on its own, so a chameleon can watch the sky for danger while also tracking an insect below. Fun fact: A chameleon's tongue can shoot out in under a hundredth of a second — faster than a human eye can follow."
